description:
The Vanishing Boy

Jimmy Blackton knew that the Police had him dead to rights, that he deserved to go to prison, yet he swore never to pay for his crime! But when Jimmy learned that you can never run away from yourself, a marvelous change came over him!

The Message (Text Only Story)

The Man Who Shrunk

Some people have spent their lives trying to find a way to defeat tyranny! Others have given their lives to remove a dictator! But until now no one thought of ending dictatorships with a cake of soap!

Man On Mars!

He faced the stars with eagerness, and Mars, the Red Planet winked back at him with promise! There was man's heritage, his goal of the future! Yet, would he come destroying and arrogant, or filled with the humbleness of beauty? The answer waitied for... Man on Mars!

It Wouldn't Let Go

Phil Jamison told a lie, and he was stuck with it! But when he found courage to tell the truth, he was relieved of his troublesome burden, for Phil's confession had an amazing effect on his boss!

The Thing in the Crate!

The people in this country have seen a lot of conventions, but none ever came close to matching the startling meeting he held in a ranch house! The first notice of that astonishing get-together was... The Thing in the Crate!

description:
Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following four stories:

  • The Day They Stole My Face!
  • I Was the Last Man on Earth!
  • The Jungle's Bravest Beasts!
  • The Queen and I!

The issue also features several small comic strips:

  • Professor Eureka
  • Binky in 'Healthy Teeth for You and Your Pet'
  • Moolah the Mystic

The Day They Stole My Face

Henry Wood and his family are the average american family; however, their new neighbors want to change that. When Henry heads to work on day he realizes that there is an exact replica of his family in the house next door, confronting his own doppelganger he learns that they're aliens and they've got a terrible plan for Earth! Will Henry be able to stop them before it's too late?

I Was the Last Man on Earth

Arthur Thompkins, Chief Astronomer of the national institute is performing a unique experiment regarding a solar eclipse while in a bathysphere 10,000 fathoms under the sea. When he arises he realizes he's the only man on Earth, is it all a dream or did something strange happen while Arthur was down under?

The Jungles Bravest Beasts

A pack of big game hunters look at the awesome power of elephants, lionesses and chimps!

The Queen and I

An undiscovered actress known only as Moria Fate steps up to play the lead role in a movie, a wondrous queen named Queen Zapita. Fate is a natural; however, things begin to get a little strange when no records exist of her true identification and she knows more about the character than anyone else!

Professor Eureka

The Professor visits Doctor Fendel who has designed a new robot, but he might have made it a tad too smart!

Binky in 'Healthy Teeth for You and Your Pet'

Binky teaches readers the importance of good hygiene for both humans and animals!

Moolah the Mystic

Moolah gets a job at a sandwich shop.
name: The Queen and I
